events.name: Stanford Cardinal at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Kenny Hill passed for two touchdowns, ran for another and even caught one as No. 13 TCU rallied from a big early deficit to beat 15th-ranked Stanford 39-37 in the Alamo Bowl on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 13 TCU and Hill rally to beat No. 15 Stanford 39-37

video.headline: TCU's huge second-half earns Alamo Bowl win

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Michigan State Spartans

notes.headline: SAN DIEGO COUNTY CREDIT UNION HOLIDAY BOWL

headlines.description: Brian Lewerke threw for 213 yards and three touchdowns, and LJ Scott ran for 110 yards and two scores for No. 18 Michigan State, which took advantage of Luke Falk's absence to rout No. 21 Washington State 42-17 in the Holiday Bowl on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lewerke, Spartans roll past Cougars 42-17 in Holiday Bowl

video.headline: Michigan State's Lewerke goes deep for TD

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Mason Rudolph threw for 351 yards and a pair of touchdowns, James Washington became Oklahoma State's career receiving yards leader and the 17th-ranked Cowboys beat No. 22 Virginia Tech 30-21 in the Camping World Bowl on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cowboy up: Oklahoma State gets past Virginia Tech, 30-21

notes.headline: MILITARY BOWL PRESENTED BY NORTHROP GRUMMAN

headlines.description: Backup quarterback Zach Abey scored five touchdowns, Malcolm Perry ran for 114 yards and two scores and Navy beat Virginia 49-7 in a surprisingly lopsided Military Bowl on Thursday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Abey's 5 TDs help Navy beat Virginia 49-7 in Military Bowl
